Preheat the #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Pop the @Mixed Peppers and Red Onion{1%pack} and @McCain Home Chips{400%g} onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Sprinkle over half the @North Indian Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

Bake on the middle shelf, ~{25-30%mins}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, lay the @Salmon Fillets{2}, skin-side down, onto a lined baking tray. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Sprinkle over the remaining spice mix. Drizzle with some @oil{} and rub to coat.

When the veg has 15 mins left, roast the salmon on the top shelf, ~{10-15%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw fish. Cook so it's opaque in the middle.

Stir the @Peas{120%g} and half the @Mango Chutney{40%g} through the roasted veg. Return to the oven for ~{1-2%mins}.

Share your sticky veg between your bowls and top with the salmon. Spoon the remaining mango chutney over the salmon.

Drizzle over the @Greek Style Natural Yoghurt{75%g} and crumble over the @Greek Style Salad Cheese{100%g} to finish.

Enjoy!